\n# => usuarios POST   /users(.:format)   {:controller=>\"users\", :action=>\"create\"}\n\n# Devise\ndevise_for :users, :as => \"usuarios\"\n# => new_user_session GET    /usuarios/sign_in  {:controller=>\"devise/sessions\", :action=>\"new\"}\n```\n\nSo, the `:as` in Rails edge is  used for naming the route, but the `:as` in `devise_for` is for generating the URL. I think devise should swap to be consistent with Rails.\n","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/heartcombo/devise/issues/199/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/heartcombo/devise/issues/199/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}